Vincent Townsend SMITH v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 3917. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. June 30, 1949. Lawrence S. Holmes, Wichita, Kan., for appellant. Lester Luther, U. S. Atty., and V. J. Bowersock, Asst. U. S. Atty., Topeka, Kan., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge, and SYMES, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed June 30, 1949, on motion of appellant.
